        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 7:40PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 739 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clegg, or 17 miles southwest of George West, moving southwest at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Clegg.

This includes US Highway 59 between mile markers 734 and 748.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
